longBusinessSummary: Seibu Holdings Inc. engages in the urban and regional transportation, hotel and leisure, real estate, construction, and other businesses in Japan and internationally. It operates through Urban Transportation and Regional, Hotel and Leisure, Real Estate, Construction, Hawaii Business, and Other Business segments. The company offers railway, bus, and taxi transportation services; operates hotels, golf courses, ski resorts, and leisure facilities; develops Seibu Railway lines and hotel sites in city centers; leases office and residential facilities; and develops and operates stores in train stations, shopping malls, and other commercial facilities. It is also involved in the construction of railway lines, social infrastructure, hotel remodeling, private sector construction, and housing. In addition, the company produces, processes, and sells gravel, sand, and other raw materials used in civil engineering and construction projects; designs and executes landscaping projects; and maintains and operates state-run parks. Further, the company operates express ways and cruise ships; and maintains a professional baseball team. Additionally, the company offers housekeeping, child-rearing support, home, urban development, and other services; and insurance products, as well as builds cemeteries. The company operates a network of 47 hotels. Seibu Holdings Inc. was founded in 2006 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
